Still looking for the last card in my NY American set.  Thanks for looking!!

Tim
Tim, I know its not a 3 but there is a 2 on Ebay now [url]http://www.ebay.com/itm/310368400090?ssPageName=STRK:MEWAX:IT&_trksid=p3984.m1423.l2649[/url] Not my card just passing it along..:)

Also an SGC40 on eBay right now.....I know it's not PSA, but I would think it would crossover to PSA without a problem.

A tough card that doesn't really come up very often.....
Yes, thanks.  Watching them both.  The sgc40 seems pretty beat up around the edges....

Thanks to Bill (bbsports), I have completed my T206 NY American set (minus the other Doyle).  28 cards total, all PSA with an avg grade of 5.2. Now I can move on, but also improve this set when I can.  I got several cards from board members and wish to thank them for the help.  

Here is the link if anyone cares.....

[url]http://www.psacard.com/PSASetRegistry/alltimeset.aspx?s=97637[/url]
